# Diff Patterns — Advanced Composition

## Diff Sources in nyne

| Source | Path pattern | When generated |
|-|-|-|
| Code actions (LSP) | `Foo@/actions/*.diff` | After diagnostics from a write |
| Rename preview | `Foo@/rename/new_name.diff` | On-demand (lookup-only, read to generate) |

All are standard unified diff format (`---`/`+++`/`@@` headers).

## Applying Diffs

```sh
# Single diff
patch -p1 < file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/10-fix.diff

# All code actions for a symbol
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/*.diff | patch -p1

# All code actions across a file
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/*@/actions/*.diff | patch -p1

# Project-level rename
patch -p1 < file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old@/rename/new.diff

# Multi-file diff
patch -p1 < big-refactor.diff

# Alternative: git apply
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/rename/new.diff | git apply
```

## Inspecting Diffs Before Applying

Always preview non-trivial diffs:

```sh
# Read the diff
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/rename/handle.diff

# Check how many files are affected
grep "^---" file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/rename/handle.diff | wc -l

# Check for specific patterns in the diff
grep "TODO\|FIXME\|HACK" file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/rename/handle.diff
```

## Editing Diffs Before Applying

Diffs are text files. Edit them to customize before applying:

```sh
# Read a code action diff
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/actions/10-update-caller.diff > /tmp/custom.diff

# Edit it (e.g., change a placeholder value)
sed -i 's/Duration::default()/Duration::from_secs(30)/' /tmp/custom.diff

# Apply the customized diff
patch -p1 < /tmp/custom.diff
```

## Combining Diffs

```sh
# Concatenate multiple diffs into one
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/10-fix.diff \
    file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Bar@/actions/10-fix.diff \
    > /tmp/combined.diff

# Apply as one operation
patch -p1 < /tmp/combined.diff
```

## Error Handling

Failed hunks are reported by `patch` on stderr. Common issues:
- **Stale diff:** Source changed since diff was generated. Re-read the preview path to regenerate.
- **Conflict:** Overlapping hunks from multiple diffs. Apply sequentially or combine manually.
- **Fuzz/offset:** `patch` will report fuzz or offset when context lines shifted — review the result.

## When to Use Diffs

Diffs are best for LSP-generated changes (code actions, renames). For direct symbol
edits, use the Edit tool on symbol bodies. For symbol deletion, use `rmdir`.
